			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>Principled Syntactic Code Completion using Placeholders</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LuísEduardodeSouzaAmorim.html">Luís Eduardo de Souza Amorim</a>, <a href="../profile/SebastianErdweg.html">Sebastian Erdweg</a>, <a href="../profile/GuidoWachsmuth.html">Guido Wachsmuth</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997374">10.1145/2997364.2997374</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It proposes IDE/editor support for principled syntactic code completion as a language tool feature.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The aim is to improve developer efficiency and interaction quality during editing (usability).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> It discusses language-aware completion that respects the language’s syntactic design constraints.
</li></ul></li></ul>
